Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with @veggie stock concentrate{1} and enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve 1⁄2 cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to #pot{}. Mash with @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} and @butter{1%TBSP} until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season generously with @salt{generously} and @pepper{generously}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Roasted Broccoli ==

While potatoes cook, cut @broccoli{1} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and crispy, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> Trim and discard woody bottom ends from asparagus or trim green beans if necessary. Swap in asparagus or green
> beans for broccoli; roast until tender and lightly browned, 10-12 minutes. (Save broccoli for another use.)

== Smoky Barramundi ==

While broccoli roasts, pat @barramundi{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Rub each fillet with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}. Season generously all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then rub @smoked paprika{1%teaspoon} into flesh sides.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add barramundi, skin sides down; cook until skin is crispy, ~{3%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Transfer barramundi, skin sides down, to a second lightly oiled baking sheet. Roast on middle rack until cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}.

== Brown Butter ==

Meanwhile, heat pan used for barramundi over medium heat. Add @butter{2%TBSP} and scallion whites. Cook, carefully swirling butter, until foamy and flecked with amber brown bits, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat and add a big squeeze of lemon juice. Stir in lemon zest; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Divide mashed potatoes, barramundi, and broccoli between plates. Top potatoes and barramundi with brown butter and sprinkle with scallion greens. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> If brown butter is done before the rest of the meal, reheat over low heat, stirring, for 1 minute.

> Fish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.